Description.text: The walnut wood card tray is precision milled to perfectly fit a stack of Focus cards. The powder coated steel divider separates active cards from new ones, or can be used to archive important task lists.

Features.description: Solid walnut base with rare earth magnets and powder coated steel card cover

Features.name: Finish
Features.description: Hand sanded and finished with natural oil

Features.name: Includes

Features.name: Considerations

SubHeader.text: The perfect pairing for an afternoon in the park under the sun. We are focused on making wines complex & easy to drink.
We will let you know once we have more wine.
No park visit is complete without the essentials.  Rep Park Cellars in your daily life.

ProductItem0.title: Fleece Pullover (Black/L)
ProductItem0.description: We believe three words says it all.  Make sure everyone else knows. Certified dog friendly too.

ProductItem1.title: Park Cellars Hat (Black)
ProductItem1.description: Just like Old Dominion, we love snapbacks.  But really, who doesn't?

ProductItem2.title: Fleece Pullover (Carbon Grey/M)
ProductItem2.description: We believe three words says it all.  Make sure everyone else knows. Certified dog friendly too.

ProductItem3.title: Dad Hat (White)
ProductItem3.description: I'm not a regular dad, I'm a cool dad that drinks wine in parks.

SubHeader.text: Our winemaking simply enhances the terroir.

BodyText.text: A light touch in the winery allows the true expression of the grapes to shine, but sometimes they need a little nudge.  That is where we come in!

SubHeader.text: Stomping allows gentle flavor extraction.

BodyText.text: Foot stomping allows us to extract a little bit more color from the grapes prior to pressing.  It's cold! But the reduced tannic structure of the wine allows us to maintain a beautiful levity in the final product.

SubHeader.text: We believe simplicity often leads to the best wine.

BenefitItem30.description: Our focus in the winery is minimal intervention.  Wine is made in the vineyard.  Everything we do in the winery is meant to bring out the characteristic of the unique sites we work with.

BenefitItem31.description: Wine should be fun! We are committed to providing you all with fun & interesting in a very easy format. Cans perhaps?  We want to get as many people drinking wine as possible.

BenefitItem32.description: We look for and work with small, locally owned and operated vineyards.  We are particularly focused on sites that are ethically farmed and leveraging vineyard best practices.
